Calculate Interaction Statistics

Source: R/interact.R

Expensive crunching behind interaction statistics such as:

  • Friedman and Popescu's \(H^2_j\) of overall interaction strength per feature.

  • Friedman and Popescu's \(H^2_{jk}\) of pairwise interaction strengths.

  • Unnormalized pairwise statistic \(H_{jk}\).

Arguments

object

Fitted model object.

...

Additional arguments passed to pred_fun(object, X, ...), for instance type = "response" in a glm() model.

v

Vector of feature names.

X

A data.frame or matrix serving as background dataset.

pred_fun

Prediction function of the form function(object, X, ...), providing K >= 1 numeric predictions per row. Its first argument represents the model object, its second argument a data structure like X. Additional arguments (such as type = "response" in a GLM) can be passed via .... The default, stats::predict(), will work in most cases. Note that column names in a resulting matrix of predictions will be used as default column names in the results.

pairwise_m

Number of features for which pairwise statistics are calculated. The features are selected based on Friedman and Popescu's overall interaction strength \(H^2_j\) (rowwise maximum in the multivariate case). Set to length(v) to not miss any pairwise interaction. Set to 0 to not calculate any pairwise interaction.

n_max

If X has more than n_max rows, a random sample of n_max rows is selected from X. In this case, set a random seed for reproducibility.

w

Optional vector of case weights for each row of X.

verbose

Should a progress bar be shown? The default is TRUE.

Value

An object of class "interact" containing these elements:

  • f: Matrix with predictions.

  • mean_f2: (Weighted) mean f^2. Used to normalize most statistics.

  • F_j: List of matrices, each representing univariable PDs.

  • F_not_j: List of matrices, each representing the PDs of all variables != j.

  • F_jk: List of matrices, each representing bivariate PDs.

  • w: Same as input w.

  • H2_j: Matrix of Friedman and Popescu's \(H^2_j\).

  • v: Same as input v.

  • v_pairwise: Subset of v with largest H2_j used for pairwise calculations.

  • combs: List of variable pairs for which pairwise PDs are available.

Methods (by class)

  • interact(default): Default interact method.

  • interact(ranger): Method for "ranger" models.

  • interact(Learner): Method for "mlr3" models.

References

Friedman, Jerome H., and Bogdan E. Popescu. "Predictive Learning via Rule Ensembles." The Annals of Applied Statistics 2, no. 3 (2008): 916-54.
